# Role & Team Based Access Control (RBAC) System

This plan outlines how we will rebuild the Organization and User Login system into a fully scalable Team and Role-Based structure, complete with an email invitation flow.

## 1. Flow Chart
Here is the step-by-step visual flow of the new invitation and permission system:

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Admin
    participant App as LeadFlow App
    participant DB as Database
    actor Invitee as Invited User

    Note over Admin,DB: 1. Admin Invites User
    Admin->>App: Clicks "Invite Member"
    Admin->>App: Enters Email, Selects Team (e.g. Sales) & Role (Leader/Member)
    App->>DB: Generates secure Invite Token & saves pending invite
    App-->>Admin: Generates Email Draft with unique Link
    Admin->>Invitee: Sends Email to Invitee

    Note over Invitee,App: 2. Invitee Creates Account
    Invitee->>App: Clicks link in email (redirected to LeadFlow)
    App->>App: Verifies Token & shows "Welcome to Organization"
    Invitee->>App: Creates Account & Logs In
    App->>DB: Consumes token, adds user to Org with Team & Role

    Note over Invitee,DB: 3. Permissions Take Effect
    alt is Leader
        Invitee->>App: Can add new Leads
        Invitee->>App: Can assign Leads to members in their Team
        Invitee->>App: Can invite new members to their Team
    else is Member
        Invitee->>App: Can only view & edit Leads assigned to them
        Invitee->>App: Cannot reassign leads or invite users
    end
```

## 2. Proposed Changes

### A. Database Schema Updates
1. **Roles Update**: I will update the system roles from `(owner, member)` to:
   - `Admin` (Has total control over the organization).
   - `Leader` (Manages a specific team, can add leads, assign leads, and invite members to their team).
   - `Member` (Can only work on leads assigned specifically to them).
2. **Teams Table**: I will create a new `teams` table (e.g., "Sales", "Marketing") so that users can be grouped together.
3. **Invitations Table**: I will create a new `invitations` table to securely store pending email invites along with their intended Team and Role.

### B. UI: Invite Modal & Email Sending
I will completely rebuild the "Invite Member" popup. 
- You will be able to enter the person's **Email Address**.
- You will select their **Team** from a dropdown.
- You will select their **Role** (Leader or Member).
- When you click "Send Invite", it will generate a secure link and automatically open your default Email Client (e.g. Gmail, Outlook) with a pre-written welcome email containing the link! *(This avoids needing expensive 3rd-party email servers while keeping it extremely professional).*

### C. Permission Enforcements
- **Admins**: Can see all leads, assign anyone to anything, create teams, and invite anyone.
- **Leaders**: When they open a lead, they can only assign it to people within their own Team. They can also add new members, but only to their Team.
- **Members**: When they log in, their Lead Pipeline will only show leads that have been specifically assigned to them. They cannot see the "Assign To" dropdown.

